goals.question: What is the relationship between precipitation and temperature range?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of precipitation vs temperature range
goals.rationale: This helps to identify any correlation between precipitation and temperature range.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='precipitation', kde=True, bins=30)
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['precipitation'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of precipitation across all locations?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x='location', y='wind', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the average wind speed vary across different locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('Wind Speed (km/h)')
    plt.legend(title='Locations', labels=data['location'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='temp_max', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend in maximum temperature over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Maximum Temperature (Celsius)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='precipitation', y='temp_range', hue='location')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between precipitation and temperature range?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Location')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    weather_counts = data.groupby(['location', 'weather']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    weather_counts_pivot = weather_counts.pivot_table(index='location', columns='weather', values='count', fill_value=0)
    
    ax = weather_counts_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title("How does the weather condition vary across different locations?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Location")
    plt.ylabel("Count")
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend(title="Weather Condition")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
